---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = "Terms of Service | RoasBodhi";
const pageDescription = "Legally binding Terms of Service for Namaste Sales Enterprises (operating as RoasBodhi™) in accordance with the Indian Contract Act 1872.";
---

<BaseLayout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} noIndex={true}>
  
  <Header />

  <main class="flex-grow pt-32 pb-24 bg-neutral-ghost text-neutral-charcoal text-left">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <div class="mb-12 border-b border-neutral-mist pb-8">
        <span class="px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-primary-saffron/10 text-primary-saffron text-[10px] font-display font-extrabold uppercase tracking-widest">
          Legal Contract
        </span>
        <h1 class="font-display font-extrabold text-neutral-dark text-3xl sm:text-5xl mt-3 tracking-tight">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="font-body text-xs text-neutral-stone mt-2 font-semibold">
          Last Updated: July 18, 2026
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none font-body text-neutral-charcoal/90 leading-relaxed space-y-8 select-none">
        
        <!-- SECTION 1 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            1. AGREEMENT AND ACCEPTANCE
          </h2>
          <p>
            This Terms of Service document (hereinafter referred to as the "Agreement" or "Terms") constitutes a legally binding contract between **Namaste Sales Enterprises** (doing business as **RoasBodhi**, hereinafter referred to as the "Company", "we", "us", or "our") and any person, company, or legal entity (hereinafter referred to as the "Client", "you", or "your") accessing our website, subscribing to our services, or purchasing deliverables.
          </p>
          <p>
            By visiting our website (<a href="https://roasbodhi.in" class="text-primary-saffron hover:underline font-semibold">https://roasbodhi.in</a>), engaging our team, confirming orders via WhatsApp, or making payments, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to be bound by all clauses in this Agreement. If you are entering into this Agreement on behalf of a company, partnership, or other corporate entity, you represent and warrant that you hold the legal authority to bind such entity to these Terms. If you do not possess such authority, or if you do not agree with any part of these Terms, you must not accept this Agreement and must immediately stop using our services.
          </p>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to amend, update, or replace any part of these Terms at our sole discretion. Any revisions will be published on this page with an updated "Last Updated" date. Your continued engagement of our services or access to our website following the posting of modifications constitutes your binding acceptance of those changes.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 2 -->
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            2. DEFINITIONS
          </h2>
          <p>
            To ensure absolute clarity, the following terms shall have the specific meanings assigned to them in this section:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2.5 text-xs">
            <li>**"Company", "We", "Us", or "Our"** refers to **Namaste Sales Enterprises**, a registered business entity based in Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra, India, operating under the brand name **RoasBodhi**.</li>
            <li>**"Client", "You", or "Your"** refers to any individual, business owner, partner, or authorized corporate representative who uses our website or commissions our services.</li>
            <li>**"Services"** refers to the digital marketing agency services offered by the Company, including Meta Ads Management, Google Ads Management, Website Design & Development, Google My Business (GMB) Optimization, Performance Marketing, and Social Media Marketing.</li>
            <li>**"Website"** refers to the official domain <a href="https://roasbodhi.in" class="text-primary-saffron hover:underline font-semibold">https://roasbodhi.in</a> and all associated pages, directories, and programmatic location subdomains.</li>
            <li>**"Content"** refers to text, images, logos, copy, testimonials, and video assets provided by either party.</li>
            <li>**"Deliverables"** refers to final customized assets created by us for you, such as website mockups, landing pages, code files, and ad graphic designs.</li>
            <li>**"Ad Spend"** refers to the actual advertising budget paid directly by the Client to advertising networks (Meta Ads, Google Ads). This is separate from our Management Fee.</li>
            <li>**"Management Fee"** refers to the service fee charged by the Company for setting up, managing, monitoring, and optimizing your campaigns or constructing your website.</li>
            <li>**"Business Days"** refers to Monday through Saturday, excluding gazetted public holidays in India.</li>
            <li>**"Aseem Revisions"** refers to our proprietary model of structured, reasonable revision cycles, defined under Section 8.</li>
            <li>**"Pay-After-Seeing"** refers to our zero-advance billing layout for website design services, defined under Section 7.</li>
            <li>**"Bodhi Utsav"** refers to promotional, seasonal, or launch package offers run by the Company.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 3 -->
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            3. SCOPE OF SERVICES
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              3A. Web Design Services
            </h3>
            <p>
              We design and construct high-speed static websites using frameworks like Astro.js. The exact deliverables (number of pages, features, integrations) depend on your selected plan (Ankur, Vriddhi, or Siddhi).
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>**Client-Provided Content:** The Client is solely responsible for providing all text, brand logos, high-resolution product images, and legal licensing permissions.</li>
              <li>**Design Approvals:** We build a working preview of your website on a temporary test URL. Once you approve the preview and complete the payment, we register your domain and launch the site live.</li>
              <li>**Post-Launch Support:** Every web project includes a basic support period (ranging from 14 to 60 days based on the plan) covering minor bug fixes and text adjustments. Standard maintenance beyond this window is chargeable.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              3B. Ad Management Services
            </h3>
            <p>
              We manage Meta Ads, Google Ads, and GMB Optimization packages.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>**Separate Ad Budgets:** Ad Spend is paid directly by the Client to Meta or Google using their own billing methods. Our service covers strategy, ad copywriting, graphic setup, optimization, and monthly reports.</li>
              <li>**Platform Access:** The Client must grant us appropriate partner or admin access to their Meta Business Manager, Google Ads accounts, and Google Business Profile. We are not liable for delayed launches if access is delayed.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              3C. What We Do NOT Do
            </h3>
            <p>
              Unless explicitly specified in writing, our services **do not include**:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>Original copy editing, product photography, or professional raw videography.</li>
              <li>Guarantees of specific page rankings on search engines or specific conversion rates.</li>
              <li>Verifying legal compliance of the Client's business models, products, or industry permits.</li>
              <li>Customer service or operations support for the Client's end-users.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 4 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            4. CLIENT OBLIGATIONS
          </h2>
          <p>
            To ensure successful campaign setups and web rollouts, the Client agrees to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-xs">
            <li>Provide accurate, complete, and truthful information about their business, legal name, and contact coordinates.</li>
            <li>Deliver all necessary design inputs, media files, and branding assets within **5 business days** of project onboarding. Delayed inputs will result in project timeline extensions.</li>
            <li>Provide review feedback within **48 hours** of receiving revision drafts. Silence beyond 7 days on drafts will result in automatic project closure.</li>
            <li>Make all invoice payments on or before the due date.</li>
            <li>Maintain all municipal, state, and central business licenses required to operate in their sector.</li>
            <li>File their own GST returns and manage their respective business tax obligations.</li>
            <li>Refrain from engaging in any illegal activities or using our marketing pipelines to distribute misleading claims.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 5 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            5. PROHIBITED INDUSTRIES
          </h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to refuse service to any entity. We do not manage campaigns or design websites for businesses involved in:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
            <li>Adult content, pornography, or escort services.</li>
            <li>Illegal drugs, narcotics, or unregulated health supplements.</li>
            <li>Weapons, ammunition, and explosives.</li>
            <li>Unlicensed gambling, betting portals, or lottery systems.</li>
            <li>Cryptocurrency, NFT projects, or speculative get-rich-quick schemes.</li>
            <li>Multi-level marketing (MLM) structures or pyramid investment networks.</li>
            <li>Counterfeit products or copyright-infringing merchandise.</li>
            <li>Hate speech, political extremism, or discriminatory media.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 6 -->
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            6. PAYMENT TERMS
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              6A. Website Projects (Pay-After-Seeing)
            </h3>
            <p>
              We build your website preview with **₹0 advance payment**.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>Once you approve the design preview, the full package price becomes due.</li>
              <li>All payments must clear before we register custom domains, transfer file directories, or launch the live site.</li>
              <li>Late payments accrue interest at a rate of **2% per month** from the invoice date.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              6B. Ad Management Services
            </h3>
            <p>
              Ad management retainer fees are billed **monthly in advance**.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>One-time setup fees are non-refundable once campaign planning starts.</li>
              <li>All services require a **3-month minimum contract** to allow for campaign stabilization and optimization.</li>
              <li>Retainers auto-renew monthly unless cancelled via written notice at least **15 days** before the next billing date.</li>
              <li>Late payments have a **5-day grace period**. Beyond this, campaigns will be paused. Paused accounts require a **₹2,000 reactivation fee** to resume management.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              6C. Accepted Payment Methods
            </h3>
            <p>
              All payments are processed securely via **Razorpay**. We accept UPI, Net Banking, and major Debit/Credit cards. Under standard financial compliance, we **do not accept cash or physical cheques**.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              6D. GST and Taxes
            </h3>
            <p>
              All service prices listed are **exclusive of GST**. An 18% Goods and Services Tax (GST) will be added to all invoices. Clients wishing to claim input tax credit must provide their valid GSTIN details at onboarding.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 7 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            7. THE "PAY-AFTER-SEEING" MODEL
          </h2>
          <p>
            Our web design projects follow a risk-free development pipeline:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 text-xs">
            <li>**Service Request:** Client orders a plan and submits brand assets and content requirements.</li>
            <li>**Preview Build:** We construct a complete homepage and site draft and host it on a temporary test URL.</li>
            <li>**Review & Decision:** The Client has **7 business days** to review the preview.
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mt-1 space-y-1">
                <li>**Option A (Approval):** If approved, the Client pays the invoice, and we move files to their live domain.</li>
                <li>**Option B (Rejection):** If rejected with valid written reasons, we terminate the project immediately. The Client owes us nothing, and we delete the preview files.</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>**Silence Clause:** If the Client fails to respond within 7 days, the project is marked closed. We reserve the right to decline future requests from that entity.</li>
            <li>**IP Protection:** In case of rejection, the Client holds **no rights** to the layout, design patterns, custom copy, or elements of the preview site. Any unauthorized replication of our preview designs will result in immediate legal action.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 8 -->
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            8. REVISION POLICY ("ASEEM" REVISIONS)
          </h2>
          <p>
            While we offer generous revision guidelines, the term **"Aseem" (असीम)** refers to structured, reasonable updates within the original project scope, and is not a license for unlimited redesigns.
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              8A. Web Design Revisions
            </h3>
            <p>
              Revisions are structured in rounds based on your selected plan:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>**Ankur Plan:** Up to **5 revision rounds**.</li>
              <li>**Vriddhi Plan:** Up to **8 revision rounds**.</li>
              <li>**Siddhi Plan:** Up to **12 revision rounds**.</li>
              <li>**Definition of a Round:** A single revision round consists of the Client submitting **one consolidated list** of adjustments. Submitting edits across multiple separate emails will be counted as separate rounds. All requested changes must fit within the scope defined at onboarding. Complete layout redesigns after draft approval require a new quote.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              8B. Ad Campaign Revisions
            </h3>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 text-xs">
              <li>Includes **1 major revision** per creative design package.</li>
              <li>Target audience configurations and strategies are reviewed and optimized monthly. Additional design requests outside the monthly retainer allotment are billed at **₹500 to ₹1,500 per creative asset**.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 9 -->
        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            9. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              9A. Our Intellectual Property
            </h3>
            <p>
              The RoasBodhi brand name, leaf logo mark, website content, software scripts, custom sitemap configurations, and workflow methodologies are the sole intellectual property of Namaste Sales Enterprises. We reserve the right to reference completed projects, metrics, and Client testimonials in our case studies and promotional media.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-2">
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-sm text-neutral-dark">
              9B. Ownership Transfer
            </h3>
            <p>
              The Client owns their brand assets, logos, and raw copy. Ownership of final web deliverables transfers to the Client **only after all outstanding invoices are paid in full**. Until payment is cleared, the copyright of all source code, assets, and layouts remains with us.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 10 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            10. NO GUARANTEE OF RESULTS
          </h2>
          <p>
            Digital marketing is subject to dynamic market variables, user behavior, and platform algorithm changes. Consequently, the Company **does not guarantee**:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
            <li>Specific page positions or search rankings on Google Search.</li>
            <li>Specific Return on Ad Spend (ROAS) multipliers.</li>
            <li>A guaranteed volume of leads, phone inquiries, or retail sales.</li>
            <li>A fixed conversion rate for landing pages.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Campaign performance is dependent on several factors outside our control, including your product quality, pricing, competitor budgets, local market conditions, and how quickly your sales team contacts inbound leads. All past performance metrics shared in our case studies are illustrative examples of past client success and do not constitute a promise or guarantee of future returns.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 11 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            11. THIRD-PARTY PLATFORM RISKS
          </h2>
          <p>
            Our services rely on third-party networks (Meta, Google, Instagram, WhatsApp). You acknowledge that these platforms enforce their own policies and terms of service:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
            <li>Meta or Google may pause, disable, or ban advertising accounts at their sole discretion. We are not liable for any account restrictions, ads manager suspensions, or post removals.</li>
            <li>We are not responsible for platform service interruptions, policy changes, API adjustments, or billing increases.</li>
            <li>The Client is responsible for paying all ad spends incurred, regardless of account restrictions.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 12 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            12. CONFIDENTIALITY
          </h2>
          <p>
            Both parties agree to treat all business plans, access details, pricing formulas, and customer records shared during the engagement as confidential. Neither party shall disclose this information to any third party without written consent, except when required by law. This confidentiality obligation remains in effect for **3 years** following the termination of our services.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 13 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            13. WARRANTIES AND REPRESENTATIONS
          </h2>
          <p>
            **Client Warranties:** The Client warrants that they have the legal authority to enter into this contract, that they own the rights to all media and copy assets provided to us, and that their business operations comply with all local, state, and national laws.
          </p>
          <p>
            **Our Warranties:** We warrant that we will deliver all services with reasonable professional skill and diligence. We make no other warranties, express or implied, regarding the performance or commercial suitability of our deliverables.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 14 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            14. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
          </h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Namaste Sales Enterprises, its directors, and employees shall not be liable for any indirect, special, incidental, or consequential damages, including loss of profits, revenue, data, or business opportunities.
          </p>
          <p>
            **Liability Cap:** In no event shall our total cumulative liability for all claims arising out of this Agreement exceed the **total Management Fee actually paid by the Client to us during the three (3) months** immediately preceding the event that gave rise to the claim. This limit applies regardless of whether the claim is based on contract, tort, or any other legal theory.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 15 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            15. INDEMNIFICATION
          </h2>
          <p>
            The Client agrees to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless Namaste Sales Enterprises, its founders, and employees from any third-party claims, losses, damages, or legal costs arising from:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
            <li>Any intellectual property infringement claims related to Client-provided content.</li>
            <li>Claims by your customers regarding your products, services, or business operations.</li>
            <li>Your breach of any terms, obligations, or warranties in this Agreement.</li>
            <li>GST tax disputes or business registration issues on the Client's part.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 16 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            16. FORCE MAJEURE
          </h2>
          <p>
            Neither party shall be liable for delays or failures to perform obligations under this Agreement caused by events beyond their reasonable control, including natural disasters, pandemics, government shutdowns, cyber warfare, labor strikes, power grid failures, or third-party platform outages (Meta or Google server down times). If a Force Majeure event persists for more than **60 days**, either party may terminate the contract upon written notice.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 17 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            17. CANCELLATION AND TERMINATION
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-xs">
            <li>**Web Projects:** The Client can cancel web projects at any time before design approval with no charges. Setup and domain purchase fees, once processed, are non-refundable.</li>
            <li>**Ad Management Retainers:** Either party can terminate active ad services by providing a **15-day written notice** before the next billing cycle.</li>
            <li>**Termination for Cause:** We reserve the right to suspend or terminate services immediately, without notice or refund, if the Client is found in breach of this Agreement, engages in illegal activities, uses abusive behavior toward our staff, or fails to resolve outstanding invoices.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 18 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            18. DISPUTE RESOLUTION
          </h2>
          <p>
            We believe in resolving disputes amicably. The Client agrees to follow this dispute resolution process:
          </p>
          <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2 text-xs">
            <li>**Direct Discussion:** The parties will first attempt to resolve any disagreement through mutual discussions for **30 days**.</li>
            <li>**Mediation:** If direct discussion fails, the parties will participate in voluntary mediation in Navi Mumbai.</li>
            <li>**Arbitration:** If mediation fails, the dispute will be referred to binding arbitration before a single arbitrator appointed by us. The arbitration seat and venue shall be **Navi Mumbai, Maharashtra, India**, and the language of the proceedings shall be English, governed by the Indian Arbitration and Conciliation Act.</li>
            <li>**Exclusive Jurisdiction:** If legal action is required beyond arbitration, both parties agree to submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the **courts at Navi Mumbai / Thane, Maharashtra, India**.</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 19 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            19. CLASS ACTION WAIVER
          </h2>
          <p>
            You agree that any legal action or arbitration arising out of this Agreement will be conducted on an **individual basis only**. You waive the right to participate in any class action lawsuit, joint litigation, or representative arbitration against the Company.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 20 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            20. ANTI-FRAUD PROVISIONS
          </h2>
          <p>
            We monitor all transactions and account activity. We reserve the right to suspend services and pursue legal action (seeking damages up to **₹10,00,000 INR**) if we detect:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1.5 text-xs">
            <li>Submission of false corporate details or stolen payment credentials.</li>
            <li>Frivolous chargebacks or payment gate disputes intended to bypass our refund policy.</li>
            <li>Threats, extortion attempts, or bad-faith negative review campaigns aimed at forcing discounts.</li>
            <li>Attempts to copy, clone, or reverse-engineer our web code, sitemaps, or templates.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 21 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            21. NON-SOLICITATION
          </h2>
          <p>
            During the service period and for **two (2) years** following the termination of services, the Client agrees not to poach, recruit, or hire any of our developers, designers, or strategists. Any breach of this non-solicitation clause will result in an automatic penalty payment to the Company equal to **six (6) months** of the solicited employee's last drawn salary.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- SECTION 22 -->
        <section class="space-y-3">
          <h2 class="font-display font-extrabold text-lg text-neutral-dark border-l-4 border-primary-saffron pl-3">
            22. NEGATIVE REVIEW POLICY
          </h2>
          <p>
            We welcome constructive feedback. However, posting false statement, defamatory comments, or coordinated negative review campaigns on public channels (Google Maps, Facebook, Trustpilot) violates this Agreement. If a Client posts false or defamatory statements, we reserve the right to pursue all legal remedies under Section 66A of the IT Act and civil defamation laws, including seeking damages up to **₹10,00,000 INR** and obtaining court injunctions to remove the content.
          </p>
        </section>

